<LP>
   MET-PRO Corp. (Harleysville, Pa.) -- Edwin A. Wilcox was
named president and chief operating officer of this maker of
pollution-control and fluid handling systems. Mr. Wilcox, 52
years old, has previously been president of UGI Corp.'s
AmeriGas Industrial Gas unit. He had been in his most recent
position, which the company declined to identify, for two
months. Mr. Wilcox succeeds Walter A. Everett as president.
Mr. Everett, 68, will continue as chief executive officer and
will become chairman; in the latter post, he succeeds E. J.
Wofsey, 73, who was named general counsel and vice chairman.
